ed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[8154,1420],"id":"6dd4a093-2b3b-475d-b560-a027eec90612","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Lead Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[8478,1420],"id":"bbd3cd4f-db52-4336-b728-0a9ae1685f3c","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### New Lead Form Submission\n\nServes an n8n-hosted form (Email, Company, Score). Each submission becomes one execution.\n\nNext: Stamp & Shape Lead","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"c2ae9257-9540-4680-db14-eafeca44045c","name":"Note: New Lead Form Submission"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp & Shape Lead\n\nShapes the item: writes `leadId`, `receivedAt`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Payload Valid?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"e1f9c298-ef6c-405f-b612-b3511905776f","name":"Note: Stamp & Shape Lead"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Payload Valid?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.leadId }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Route by Work Type · ②→ Record Rejected Input","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"cba6b6f5-43da-4759-06f5-a11a76337982","name":"Note: Payload Valid?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Rejected Input\n\nAppends a new row to 'tracking sheet' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,1030],"id":"5f70a5db-bab4-8bae-ba2c-3c19c00daecd","name":"Note: Record Rejected Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Route by Work Type\n\nRoutes each item to one of 3 lanes: sales, support + fallback.\n\nPorts: ①→ Delegate 'sales' to Sub-workflow · ②→ Fast-Track 'support' + Alert · ③→ Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"5a8a4237-e840-8521-4508-77fa80e87537","name":"Note: Route by Work Type"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Delegate 'sales' to Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,250],"id":"8862aa50-5fdc-f68d-bbd4-356c596e9de3","name":"Note: Delegate 'sales' to Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fast-Track 'support' + Alert\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#sales`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,760],"id":"2d98753d-5456-c40b-6543-cdebcdc3ce37","name":"Note: Fast-Track 'support' + Alert"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)\n\nAppends a new row to 'Lead Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,1270],"id":"dba842ca-7ec8-5226-33c5-8abe44617091","name":"Note: Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Merge Routed Work\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,520],"id":"4784d534-9df9-40ab-3ead-280f6a842028","name":"Note: Merge Routed Work"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per lead (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3234,520],"id":"d731c9a0-becc-d721-0c6b-50163819c91e","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,520],"id":"6e2d86cd-a6e1-5ec4-a3dc-f6585a41daf0","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"01bd714f-095f-3bb6-7b6f-a80b9ec05566","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"5ef4377d-155f-89f5-1421-dbcc59026e88","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nReads every row from 'Lead Tracker' — the read side of the store, e.g. for a digest or a downstream sync.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"51ab49de-324d-dfbf-093c-2b41ae210d85","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"8f49a414-d1ce-29ee-2b9e-8791e88666fd","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"de181d96-c682-b8e2-4792-bcbff2c4267a","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"b89b9a34-2125-0400-28d9-47dc263b80f7","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"42195baf-b07d-8fe5-1bf5-1354653289d1","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"1ab61d6a-e35e-aa1f-168f-369458ebb0e4","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"81aa0887-ae5d-41f6-5a83-ba7e38522009","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Cap Batch Volume · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,520],"id":"78c30179-bf44-a608-a6e3-ec29484f6735","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 25 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,520],"id":"b8ee560d-d1b2-2924-7d41-6bd45f44ba37","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,520],"id":"ad2d5e99-129c-90de-1c62-9e1148cff5a1","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7770,520],"id":"84519f11-33b0-3dda-a3fc-07f1239ed557","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\nAppends a new row to 'Lead Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8094,520],"id":"602cf998-6384-7e9e-ff24-94d88371e88c","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#sales`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,520],"id":"74155b88-c78c-92a6-c9db-cf6e8d828b81","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7770,1540],"id":"7d8df680-7d9f-8d6b-e368-1353192539cb","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#sales`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8094,1540],"id":"ef2b4f12-5947-ca5e-1016-0855dc974a95","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nAppends a new row to 'Lead Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,1540],"id":"4dfff437-80bc-5d76-e682-e6d2a5e628cf","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Capture applications with Google Sheets and Slack without manual work\n\n**Pattern:** Form Intake · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Form\n\n## What it does\nCapture applications with Google Sheets and Slack without manual work. It starts from a hosted form submission.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual outreach is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nNew Lead Form Submission → Stamp & Shape Lead → Payload Valid? → Route by Work Type → Delegate 'sales' to Sub-workflow → Merge Routed Work → Fingerprint for Idempotency → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to form intake without manual effort\n- Anyone automating outreach in sales\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.\n\n## Try it now\nSample data is pinned on the trigger — hit **Execute Workflow** to watch it flow through every node before connecting any real credentials. Unpin the trigger (right-click → Unpin) when you're ready to go live.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"4dc59230-28fb-e157-b493-a4873d85adef","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Design decisions\n\nUnrecognized work types are parked in a dead-letter lane instead of erroring the whole run or silently dropping the item — new event kinds will show up eventually, and this is where you'd notice one without losing it. One kind is deliberately routed through a sub-workflow to show how heavier per-type logic can be extracted without touching this router at all.","width":480,"height":300,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1020],"id":"5b710e74-0801-003c-d853-5817b2edbe3b","name":"🎓 Design Decisions"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Practice exercises\n\nAbout as deep as this pattern goes — extend it:\n\n1. Send a work-type value that matches no switch rule and confirm it lands in the dead-letter branch.\n2. Add a new work type and its own handling branch.\n3. Replace the direct-write branch with a sub-workflow call, matching the pattern already used for the first kind.","width":480,"height":340,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1360],"id":"ac0c4f11-226c-c0db-ee38-cab332b83125","name":"🧪 Practice Exercises"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"18b8fa8c-05d4-5c80-b091-d98c11dafc7b","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"94059f5a-32e3-7685-24bd-b7c370114a63","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your outreach process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-290],"id":"ce3b96b6-0701-fa03-ef0d-73f36135f627","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"New Lead Form Submission":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp & Shape Lead","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp & Shape Lead":{"main":[[{"node":"Payload Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Payload Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Route by Work Type","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Record Rejected Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Route by Work Type":{"main":[[{"node":"Delegate 'sales' to Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Fast-Track 'support' + Alert","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Delegate 'sales' to Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Routed Work","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fast-Track 'support' + Alert":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Routed Work","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Routed Work","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Merge Routed Work":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1","saveDataErrorExecution":"all","saveManualExecutions":true,"executionTimeout":3600},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{"New Lead Form Submission":[{"json":{"leadId":"LEAD-8801","email":"tom.becker@innotech.com","company":"InnoTech Solutions","score":82}},{"json":{"leadId":"LEAD-8802","email":"grace.kim@harborworks.com","company":"Harborworks","score":47}}]},"versionId":"5700fa83-66fa-4853-b13d-383d3590ce57","id":"FDX04814"}